==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lynch
<hw>Lynch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Lynched</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Lynching</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See Note under <er>Lynch
law</er>.]</ety> <def>To inflict punishment upon, especially death,
without the forms of law, as when a mob captures and hangs a suspected
person. See <er>Lynch law</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lyncher</ent>⟦br⟧
